What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

`t/t_interface_clocking_breaks_assignments.pl -Wno-BLKANDNBLK`

Please not that when I run the test case without `-Wno-BLKANDBLK`, I get the following warning:
`
%Error-BLKANDNBLK: t/t_interface_clocking_breaks_assignments.v:78:49: Unsupported: Blocked and non-blocking assignments to same variable: 'arvalid'
                                                                    : ... note: In instance 't.axi5_lite'
   78 |   logic                                         arvalid;
      |                                                 ^~~~~~~
                   t/t_interface_clocking_breaks_assignments.v:114:5: ... Location of blocking assignment
  114 |     output arvalid;
      |     ^~~~~~
                   t/t_interface_clocking_breaks_assignments.v:35:19: ... Location of nonblocking assignment
   35 |         axi5_lite.arvalid <= 1;
      |                   ^~~~~~~
                   ... For error description see https://verilator.org/warn/BLKANDNBLK?v=5.027
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
` 
The supposed blocking assignment is in the clocking, which is never used in the test case, so this warning seems erroneous.

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
I ran the test case in the regression suite for commit 2f5c58b345eca4bf81cace78e9a1d867fa579eef
What OS and distribution are you using?
Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
If there is an easy fix, I would be happy to try. Otherwise, I am afraid I might break something else (especially virtual interfaces) when trying to fix this.
(Please avoid attaching screenshots that show text - you can convert images to text using e.g. https://ocr.space)
